CatDescriptText: Miss V. Lunsford, 1529 Arch Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1957, pg. 3 with question: "Does the financial aid, given young married couples by parents, encourage or dissuade the latter's realization of marital responsibilities?" answer reads: "I've never had it, so I can't say too much. I think, however, that it all depends on how much financial aid and other helps are given."
